Issues.Body:
I believe this addresses the issue mentioned in #96, by using the `AssemblyName` property on `XmlnsDefinitionAttribute` which has always been a no-op property and not worked right.

I've been able to test the parsing at runtime, but [the readme still lacks documentation](https://github.com/dotnet/wpf/blob/master/Documentation/developer-guide.md#testing-presentationbuildtasks) on how to test `PresentationBuildTasks`.

Example:
```cs
[assembly: System.Windows.Markup.XmlnsPrefix("http://schemas.xaml.dev/dotMorten/2020", "sysText")]
[assembly: System.Windows.Markup.XmlnsDefinition("http://schemas.xaml.dev/dotMorten/2020", "System.Text", AssemblyName = "System.Runtime")]

// ...

StringReader stringReader = new StringReader("<Grid xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation\" xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml\" xmlns:sysText=\"http://schemas.xaml.dev/dotMorten/2020\" ><Grid.Resources><sysText:Rune x:Key=\"rune\" /></Grid.Resources></Grid>");
XmlReader xmlReader = XmlReader.Create(stringReader);
Grid grid = (Grid)System.Windows.Markup.XamlReader.Load(xmlReader);

```
